THR the humorous/comical depiction of Paralympic Athletes Recently, the official Paralympics TikTok account has come under significant controversy for its depiction of Paralympic athletes. The videos in question consist of footage of disabled athletes competing, overlaid with trendy sounds and music, with the intent of creating a humorous depiction.
One video features Australian cyclist Darren Hicks, who had his right leg amputated after a crash, winning a time trial gold medal at Tokyo 2020. The audio is a popular TikTok song modified so that the only audible word is "left." The video has garnered 4.8 million likes.
Another video shows Chinese athlete Zhong Zhiqiang competing in the T42 long jump at the 2015 IPC World Athletic Championships, with a sound overlay that repeatedly says, “I said right foot, I said right foot.” Zhong’s right leg is the one he competes on.
In yet another video, a visually impaired US athlete reaches for his bike in the triathlon after just coming out of the water. The caption reads, “Para Triathlon is swimming, cycling, and air piano,” with a piano sound played over the top. In the comments, the official Paralympic account replied, “This is Brad Snyder. He is brilliant at triathlon and Beethoven on the air piano.”
These videos have elicited mixed reactions from both the disabled community and the general public.

THS the trend of looksmaxxing Looksmaxxing is a viral social media trend popular among teenage boys and young men that is centred around trying to maximise your physical attractiveness. Looksmaxxing can take many forms, such as “softmaxxing” which encourages using moisturiser, trimming facial hair and going to the gym. “Hardmaxxing” focuses on features that cannot be changed naturally such as height and facial structure, and promotes the use of cosmetic surgery and limb-lengthening procedures. Many exercises promoted through looksmaxxing such as “edging” and “mewing” are pseudoscientific and unlikely to work.

TH as Vimala would take the job in Qatar Vimala is a housewife living in the rural village of Rikillagaskada. Neither she nor her husband are well-educated. Vimala’s husband, Boralugoda, has a regular office job in the government sector, and is guaranteed to get a pension when he retires. The couple has two teenage children who go to the nearby Poramadulla Central College.
Recently, a foreign employment agency named Cassim Videsha Rakiya visited Vimala’s village, offering the women jobs in Qatar as housemaids. The salary is equivalent to LKR 100,000 per month and includes food, accomodation and healthcare for the worker. However, the contract is for five years and you cannot return to Sri Lanka during this period.

Assuming you are the only party in your country with access to this technology, TH as a progressive party in a developing country W use Advanced Analytics in elections

Advanced Analytics is the autonomous or semi-autonomous examination of data or content. It involves using sophisticated techniques such as machine learning algorithms, deep learning, predictive modelling, or other tools. Advanced Analytics can be used for political microtargeting, which involves identifying the detailed profile of individual voters and voter groups, testing the most persuasive messages, and tailoring campaign strategy to target different voter profiles. The personal identifiers of the individual voters is anonymized, and political parties do not have direct access to this data
